* ============================================================
* LIST_CURSOR_SHAKEDOWN.DTS
* Verifies:
*   1) LIST summary prints:
*        Cursor: Area n of 0 ... n Physical Recno n, Logical Row n
*   2) plain LIST is cursor-anchored
*   3) LIST does not advance/persist cursor movement
*   4) LIST TOP / LIST BOTTOM / LIST ALL behavior
*   5) ordered vs physical stream behavior
* ============================================================

SET ECHO OFF
ECHO ===== LIST CURSOR SHAKEDOWN START =====

COLOR DEFAULT
VERSION
WSREPORT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 0. Open community college set
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 0: OPEN =====
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
STATUS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 1. Pick a table with enough rows
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 1: STUDENTS NATURAL ORDER =====
SELECT 9
AREA
FIELDS
COUNT

ECHO ----- TOP then LIST -----
TOP
LIST

ECHO ----- LIST again: should start from same cursor because LIST restores cursor -----
LIST

ECHO ----- SKIP 5 then LIST: plain LIST should now anchor from moved cursor -----
SKIP 5
LIST

ECHO ----- LIST again: should show same starting point as prior LIST -----
LIST

ECHO ----- GO 1 then LIST -----
GO 1
LIST

ECHO ----- BOTTOM then LIST -----
BOTTOM
LIST

ECHO ----- LIST TOP -----
LIST TOP

ECHO ----- LIST BOTTOM -----
LIST BOTTOM

ECHO ----- LIST ALL -----
LIST ALL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 2. Deleted/filter interaction in physical order
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 2: FILTER / DELETED =====
TOP
SET DELETED ON
LIST

SET FILTER TO MAJOR = "CS"
TOP
LIST
COUNT

ECHO ----- move inside filtered stream and LIST again -----
SKIP 2
LIST

SET FILTER TO
SET DELETED ON
TOP
LIST

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 3. Ordered stream behavior
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 3: ORDERED STREAM =====
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST

ECHO ----- activate a tag if present -----
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
AREA
TOP
LIST

ECHO ----- plain LIST again: same cursor because LIST restores -----
LIST

ECHO ----- SKIP 3 in ordered stream, then LIST -----
SKIP 3
LIST

ECHO ----- SEEK in ordered stream, then LIST -----
SEEK "SMITH"
LIST

ECHO ----- TOP in ordered stream, then LIST -----
TOP
LIST

ECHO ----- BOTTOM in ordered stream, then LIST -----
BOTTOM
LIST

ECHO ----- LIST ALL in ordered stream -----
LIST ALL

ECHO ----- disable order, back to natural -----
SET ORDER TO 0
TOP
LIST

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 4. Another area sanity check
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 4: SECOND TABLE =====
SELECT 10
AREA
COUNT
TOP
LIST
SKIP 2
LIST
LIST TOP
LIST BOTTOM
LIST ALL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 5. Cross-area cursor line sanity
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 5: AREA NUMBER SANITY =====
SELECT 9
TOP
LIST

SELECT 10
TOP
LIST

SELECT 2
TOP
LIST

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* 6. Final workspace report
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SECTION 6: FINAL STATUS =====
STATUS
WSREPORT

ECHO ===== LIST CURSOR SHAKEDOWN END =====